[[!meta title="Installing onto a USB stick, for Windows"]]

We will be using the Universal USB Installer, for more info or more help visit
[http://www.pendrivelinux.com/](http://www.pendrivelinux.com/).

### Insert a USB stick with at least 2GB of free space

### [Download the Universal USB Installer](http://www.pendrivelinux.com/downloads/Universal-USB-Installer/Universal-USB-Installer.exe)

### Click 'Run' when prompted<br/>

![Do you want to run or save this file?](windows/01-run.jpg)

### If the security dialog appears, confirm by clicking 'Run'

![The publisher could not be verified. Are you sure you want to run this
software?](windows/02-run.jpg)

### Read the licence agreement and choose 'I Agree' to continue

![License Agreement](windows/03-license-agreement.png)

### Select T(A)ILS from the dropdown list

![Step 1: Select a Linux Distribution from the dropdown to put on your
USB](windows/04-select-tails.png)

### Click 'Browse' and open the downloaded ISO file

![Step 2: Select your tails*.iso](windows/05-browse-iso.png)</p>

### Choose the USB drive

![Step 3: Select your USB Flash Drive Letter
Only](windows/06-choose-drive.png)

### Click 'Create'

![Create](windows/07-create.png)

